<section class="faq-body">
  <div class="wrap-wide">
    <div class="faq-grid">

      <aside class="faq-nav">
        <a href="#cat-about" class="is-active">About IONIQ</a>
        <a href="#cat-ingredients">Ingredients &amp; science</a>
        <a href="#cat-usage">How to use</a>
        <a href="#cat-subscription">Subscription &amp; shipping</a>
      </aside>

      <div class="faq-col">

        <div class="faq-section" id="cat-about">
          <h2>About <em>IONIQ</em></h2>
          <details class="qa" open>
            <summary>What is IONIQ?</summary>
            <div class="body">IONIQ is a daily hydration and cellular energy sachet that combines 14+ ingredients across four supplement types — electrolytes, nootropics, minerals and antioxidants — in one product. The hero ingredient is 9× fire-roasted bamboo salt, which carries 70+ trace minerals and hydroxyl ions you can't get from any other salt source.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Who is it for?</summary>
            <div class="body">Athletes, runners, padel players and anyone who sweats for real. Also: professionals in their 30s–50s who realised the 3pm slump, brain fog and slow recovery weren't aging — they were depletion.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>How is IONIQ different from LMNT, Liquid IV, Gatorade?</summary>
            <div class="body">4–7× the sodium of most sports drinks, plus magnesium (which most don't have), 70+ trace minerals from bamboo salt, and a full clinical-dose nootropic stack none of them carry. Zero added sugar (Liquid IV has 11g; Gatorade 21–34g).</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>What does "9× fire-roasted bamboo salt" actually mean?</summary>
            <div class="body">A Korean tradition over 1,000 years old. Sea salt is packed into bamboo stalks, sealed with clay, and fired at 1,500°C inside a kiln. Then it's done again. Eight more times. After 9 cycles the salt's mineral structure is transformed: pH 12, 70+ trace minerals, hydroxyl ions.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Why "depletion" and not "aging"?</summary>
            <div class="body">Because most of the symptoms people blame on aging — brain fog, slower recovery, fragmented sleep, the afternoon energy crash — are actually mineral and nootropic depletion. They respond to replenishment in weeks, not years.</div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-section" id="cat-ingredients">
          <h2>Ingredients &amp; <em>science</em></h2>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>What's in a sachet?</summary>
            <div class="body">14+ ingredients across four categories. <strong>Electrolytes:</strong> 750mg sodium, 200mg potassium, 50mg magnesium. <strong>Minerals:</strong> 70+ trace minerals from 9× bamboo salt. <strong>Antioxidants:</strong> hydroxyl ions, ALCAR, taurine. <strong>Nootropics:</strong> Cognizin® citicoline, L-tyrosine, Rhodiola rosea. Every dose is labelled. No proprietary blends.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Does it contain sugar or sweeteners?</summary>
            <div class="body">No added sugar. Zero. The light sweetness comes from a small amount of organic stevia leaf extract. Under 10 calories per sachet.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Does it contain caffeine?</summary>
            <div class="body">No. IONIQ is completely caffeine-free. The energy you feel is from full mineral replenishment, Cognizin® citicoline and L-tyrosine — not stimulants.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Is it vegan, gluten-free, non-GMO?</summary>
            <div class="body">Yes to all three. 100% plant-based, certified gluten-free, non-GMO, no dairy, soy, nuts, no artificial colours/flavours/preservatives.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Is the bamboo salt safe?</summary>
            <div class="body">It's a food product used in Korean kitchens for over 1,000 years. Every batch is heavy-metal tested and ICP-MS verified. Gentler on the gut than table salt.</div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-section" id="cat-usage">
          <h2>How to <em>use</em> it</h2>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>When should I drink IONIQ?</summary>
            <div class="body"><strong>First thing in the morning</strong>, on an empty stomach, before your first coffee. On training days, also pre-workout (45–60min before) and within 30min after.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>How much water should I mix it with?</summary>
            <div class="body">500ml of cold water is standard. You can go up to 1L for a lighter flavour, or down to 350ml for stronger taste.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>How many sachets per day?</summary>
            <div class="body">One is enough for most people. Up to three is safe on heavy training days, in hot weather, or post-sauna.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Will it break my fast?</summary>
            <div class="body">No. Under 10 calories per sachet, zero sugar, zero sweeteners. Will not raise insulin or affect ketosis.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>When will I notice a difference?</summary>
            <div class="body">Cleaner morning energy within 3–5 days. Sharper focus, deeper sleep, faster recovery typically settle in by week 2.</div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-section" id="cat-subscription">
          <h2>Subscription <em>&amp; shipping</em></h2>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>How does the subscription work?</summary>
            <div class="body">$42/month for 30 sachets, billed monthly. 20% off vs one-time purchase, free shipping, skip/pause/cancel any time.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Can I skip a month or change frequency?</summary>
            <div class="body">Yes, any time. Log in, go to "Manage subscription," change frequency or pause indefinitely. No phone calls.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>How do I cancel?</summary>
            <div class="body">Click "Cancel" in your account dashboard. Takes 10 seconds. No fees, no questions, no friction.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>What about the 60-day guarantee?</summary>
            <div class="body">Try IONIQ for 60 days. If you don't notice cleaner energy, sharper focus, better recovery, email us — we'll refund the box. No restocking fees, no questions.</div>
          </details>
          <details class="qa">
            <summary>Where do you ship?</summary>
            <div class="body">Worldwide. Subscriptions ship free. One-time orders ship free over $50. US/UK: 2–4 days. EU: 3–6 days. UAE/Singapore: 1–3 days.</div>
          </details>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<script>
  const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-nav a');
  const sections = [...document.querySelectorAll('.faq-section')];
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
    entries.forEach(e => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        navLinks.forEach(a => a.classList.toggle('is-active', a.getAttribute('href') === '#' + e.target.id));
      }
    });
  }, { rootMargin: '-30% 0px -55% 0px' });
  sections.forEach(s => io.observe(s));
</script>
